sql:
SELECT cell_type
FROM cell_measurements
WHERE cell_type = 'epithelial';

SELECT AVG(area) AS average_area
FROM cell_measurements
WHERE cell_type = 'epithelial' AND cell_condition = 'healthy';

external_knowledge:
Epithelial cells are defined as a type of body tissue in biology; 
Active datasets refer to those that are currently being used or are up-to-date; 
Researchers, in this context, are individuals who manage and handle datasets.

sql:
SELECT name
FROM researchers
WHERE researcher_id IN (SELECT DISTINCT researcher_id FROM datasets);

external_knowledge:
- 'active datasets' refers to datasets with the status 'active'; 
- 'latest version' refers to the highest version number of each dataset;
- 'growth rate of length' is a measure of how fast the length of cells is changing.
